The Yulan magnolia is one of the most popular flowers during the Spring Festival across China. It's believed that the flower brings wealth and auspiciousness. It is native to eastern and southern China. It usually blooms from February to March, or earlier in areas with warmer weather. With an elegant appearance and a refreshing fragrance, it is perfect for decorating your home during the Spring Festival. (Artwork provided by Zhongshan Broadcasting and Television Station and artist Xiao Wei; Cover image designed by CGTN's Gao Hongmei) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)